messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
This is Gifford. Hello? Hello?
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
There's been a shooting at Safeway.
Okay, what do you mean? Where specifically is this?
In Oracle, where Gabrielle Giffords was.
Alright, was somebody shot?
Yes, a guy with a semi-automatic pistol started firing and then he ran.
Which way did he run?
He ran north past the Walgreens next to the Safeway.
Can you describe him? What was he wearing?
He was wearing a black hoodie and blue jeans.
Is anybody injured? Did you say Gabrielle Giffords was hit?
Yes, she's hit. She's still breathing, has a pulse. We have two people down, one dead.
And there are other people injured?
Yes, multiple people shot.
Alright, is the shooter white, black, Hispanic?
He's white, probably in his 20s or 30s. I didn't see his hair color because he had a beanie on.
Okay, we have help coming. What is your name, sir?
My name is Manuel Hernandez.
Are you an employee at Safeway?
No, I work for a separate company as a merchandiser. I was outside putting up product when I saw this through the window.
Okay, thank you, sir. We believe we have someone detained. I'm going to answer other 911 calls now. Thank you for your help.
Alright, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hi, I'm at the Wells Fargo and someone said there's a shooting at Safeway.
Yes, we have reports of that. Thank you.
Okay, thank you. Goodbye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yeah, it's the Safeway on Oracle and... you know.
Yes, we have reports of that. Thank you.
Okay, thank you. Bye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm at Oracle Safeway. There's been shots fired.
Yes, we have reports of that. Deputies are on the way. Thank you.
Okay, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I'm at Oracle and the Safeway shopping center.
Okay, what's going on there?
I believe there's a shooting outside the front of the Safeway.
Did you witness it?
We heard the gunshots. I'm in the Great Clips at the corner, and we heard quite a few shots.
Did you see anything?
People were running around the street. We didn't see much else.
Okay, we have deputies on the way. Stay inside and stay safe.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, I'm at 7130.
Is this about the shooting?
Yes.
Did you see anything?
No, someone else told me to call.
Did they see anything?
No, they only heard it.
Okay, we have deputies on the way. Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Is this about the shooting?
Yes. Did anyone see anything or just hear it?
I'm in the back of the pharmacy, so no.
Okay, we have deputies on the way. Stay safe.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, we have a lady having a panic attack. We're at 421 West Elm Road.
Did she witness anything?
I don't know, she just ran over here.
One moment, I'll get you to medical dispatch.
9-1-1, what's your emergency? Are you reporting the shooting?
Yes, I am.
Did you witness it? What is your name?
I did, my name is Emma McMahon.
What did you witness?
I heard gunshots and saw a man shooting. People tackled him and took away his gun.
Okay, we have deputies on the way. Stay where you are and try to get others to safety.
I'm in the Walgreens, in the back.
Good, stay safe. We're sending ambulances too.
Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency? Are you reporting the shooting?
Yes.
Did you witness it?
I did not.
Do you have anyone there who did?
I'm asking a customer now.
No, she didn't see it, she just heard it.
Okay, deputies are on the way. Stay where you are and stay safe.
Okay, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency? Are you reporting the shooting?
Yes, I am.
Did you witness it?
I was in the store. I saw a man down, that's all.
Okay, we have deputies and medical on the way. Stay safe.
Okay, we're in the back of the store.
Good, stay put until help arrives.
Okay, thank you.
